cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper discusses electronic collaboration tools and data analysis, which are relevant to several sub-categories. cs.CY (Computers and Society) is the most likely category as it covers the social and ethical aspects of computing, including collaboration. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also relevant as it covers the study of social networks and collaboration. cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of databases for data analysis. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the limitations of collaboration over data. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses the analysis of structured data.
